        "verdict": "in-progress",
        "topFinding": "Two structural fixes landed since 2026-07-08: money-path unit tests (test/money.test.js, commit 4aed8c1) closed the zero-coverage HIGH, and the orders cascade-delete plus photos-listing migrations were authored, lifting data-integrity to 72 and maintainability to 82 and nudging health 79 to 80. The launch-gate-1 risk is unchanged because src/index.js money-path logic was not touched: the Stripe webhook still records an event as processed and returns HTTP 200 before the DB write succeeds, with no server-side logging and the 10KB body cap on the webhook path, so a transient failure still strands a captured deposit with no retry or visibility. The highest-value move now is mechanical: migrations 0018 and 0019 are authored but uncommitted and not applied to prod, so the live photos-enumeration and money-trail cascade-delete exposures they fix remain open in production until committed and pushed with supabase db push. No hard-rule breach: secrets clean, RLS holds, screened-badge and buyer-privacy invariants intact.",
